Actually what I getting at, not trying to fit a 15".  I'm putting a Bay beam
in my Split with 79 Disc brakes.  I'd rather run 14" rims, but the split
window 14" rims don't look like they will clear the rotors even with the
adapters (to bring it back from 5x100 to 5x205).
I've seen some nice 15" bay rims on the market, mainly like the BRM's from
the west coast and England for a Bay bus.  it must be the offset of the Bay
rims that allow 14" rims to clear the rotors.  I could run the Bays all the
way around, the rear is a IRS using Bay housings and arms.  Right now it has
the wide 5 from a 70, but I have the complete housing and hubs from the 79 I
bought.
